item.title: Fed govt wants better deal for dairy farms
item.description: Supermarkets must increase payments to dairy farmers now suffering through the coronavirus crisis after enduring recent devastating natural disasters, the federal government says.

item.title: Two killed in Liberia gold mine collapse
item.description: Two people have been killed when an informal gold mine collapsed in western Liberia, the National Disaster Management Agency says.

item.title: NT farmers now allowed to grow hemp
item.description: Hemp crops can now be grown legally in the Northern Territory as new laws take effect.

item.title: Lockdown easing lifts metals prices
item.description: Industrial metals prices rose overnight as some countries eased coronavirus lockdown measures and oil prices jumped more than 10 per cent, but aluminium lagged, with investors worried that a collapse in demand will cause huge oversupply.

item.title: Woman critical after Sydney house fire
item.description: A woman is fighting for life with critical burns after running back into her burning western Sydney home to look for her dog.

item.title: Trump denies US role in Venezuela attack
item.description: US President Donald Trump has denied any involvement by his government in what Venezuelan officials have called a failed armed incursion.

item.title: US looks at winding down virus task force
item.description: The White House is having preliminary talks about when to wind down its coronavirus task force and may start moving coordination of the US response on to federal agencies in late May, Vice President Mike Pence says.

item.title: Airbnb to cut 1900 jobs amid travel slump
item.description: Airbnb is laying off 25 per cent of its workforce as it confronts a steep decline in global travel due to the new coronavirus.

item.title: US scientist ‘ousted over malaria drug’
item.description: A US government scientist says he was ousted from his position after raising concerns that the Trump administration wanted to "flood" coronavirus hotspots with a malaria drug.

item.title: UK has Europe’s highest virus death toll
item.description: The UK has overtaken Italy to report the highest official death toll from the new coronavirus in Europe.
